column2:
['The simplest way is to add this to the `button` tag:

    type=&quot;button&quot;

E.g.:

    &lt;button id=&quot;add_deals_button&quot; type=&quot;button&quot; class=&quot;btn btn-success&quot;&gt;&lt;/button&gt;

By default, the [`type` of `button` elements is `&quot;submit&quot;`][1], which submits the form. But if the `type` is `&quot;button&quot;`, it&#39;s just a button, not a form-submission button.


  [1]: http://www.w3.org/TR/html5/the-button-element.html#attr-button-type']

