['To generate Java source files from `.proto` files use [Protocol Buffers Plugin](https://www.xolstice.org/protobuf-maven-plugin/) which works out-of-the-box in eclipse Oxygen.

Basic usage ([see here for detailed description](https://www.xolstice.org/protobuf-maven-plugin/usage.html)):

 - make sure that native `protoc` compiler is [installed on your system](https://github.com/google/protobuf#protocol-compiler-installation)

 - update your `pom.xml` file:

    - make sure you use at least Java 6 (Java 7+ is recommended)

    - add plugin invocation

    - add the corresponding dependency for `com.google.protobuf:protobuf-java` 

 - put your .proto files inside project&#39;s `src/main/proto` directory

 - update the project (via `Maven -&gt; Update project...`)

Example `pom.xml`:

    &lt;project&gt;
      ...
      &lt;build&gt;
        &lt;plugins&gt;
          &lt;!-- Require at least Java 6 --&gt;
          &lt;plugin&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-compiler-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;version&gt;3.7.0&lt;/version&gt;
            &lt;configuration&gt;
              &lt;source&gt;1.6&lt;/source&gt;
              &lt;target&gt;1.6&lt;/target&gt;
            &lt;/configuration&gt;
          &lt;/plugin&gt;
          &lt;!-- Generate .java files from .proto definitions --&gt;
          &lt;plugin&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;org.xolstice.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;protobuf-maven-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;version&gt;0.5.1&lt;/version&gt;
            &lt;configuration&gt;
              &lt;protocExecutable&gt;/usr/local/bin/protoc&lt;/protocExecutable&gt;
            &lt;/configuration&gt;
            &lt;executions&gt;
              &lt;execution&gt;
                &lt;goals&gt;
                  &lt;goal&gt;compile&lt;/goal&gt;
                  &lt;goal&gt;test-compile&lt;/goal&gt;
                &lt;/goals&gt;
              &lt;/execution&gt;
            &lt;/executions&gt;
          &lt;/plugin&gt;
          ...
        &lt;/plugins&gt;
      &lt;/build&gt;
      &lt;dependencies&gt;
        &lt;dependency&gt;
          &lt;groupId&gt;com.google.protobuf&lt;/groupId&gt;
          &lt;artifactId&gt;protobuf-java&lt;/artifactId&gt;
          &lt;version&gt;3.5.1&lt;/version&gt;
        &lt;/dependency&gt;
        ...
      &lt;/dependencies&gt;
      ...
    &lt;/project&gt;

Some additional notes:

 - if `protoc` executable is in the PATH the `protocExecutable` configuration entry can be omitted

 - test-only protobuf message definitions can be put into project&#39;s `src/test/proto` directory

 - I recommend installing [Protocol Buffer Descriptor Editor](https://github.com/google/protobuf-dt) ([marketplace link](https://marketplace.eclipse.org/content/protobuf-dt))

Good luck!']

