['Using the [maven-javadoc-plugin][1], you cannot specify specific java classess (though you can with the javadoc utility, see below).  However, via the the [sourcepath][2] configuration option for the javadoc:javadoc goal, you can configure specific packages.  An example of this follows:

    &lt;plugin&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-javadoc-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;version&gt;2.5&lt;/version&gt;
        &lt;configuration&gt;
            &lt;charset&gt;UTF-8&lt;/charset&gt;
            &lt;docencoding&gt;UTF-8&lt;/docencoding&gt;
            &lt;docfilessubdirs&gt;true&lt;/docfilessubdirs&gt;
            &lt;links&gt;
                &lt;link&gt;http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.5.0/docs/api/&lt;/link&gt;
            &lt;/links&gt;
            &lt;show&gt;protected&lt;/show&gt;
            &lt;source&gt;1.5&lt;/source&gt;
            &lt;sourcepath&gt;${basedir}/src/main/java/com/acme/foo&lt;/sourcepath&gt;
        &lt;/configuration&gt;
        &lt;reportSets&gt;
            &lt;reportSet&gt;
                &lt;reports&gt;
                    &lt;report&gt;javadoc&lt;/report&gt;
                &lt;/reports&gt;
            &lt;/reportSet&gt;
        &lt;/reportSets&gt;
    &lt;/plugin&gt;

In this example, all classes under the **com.acme.foo** package (including subpackages) will have javadoc generated.

It should be noted that this Maven plugin is simply a wrapper around [Sun&#39;s javadoc utility][3].  As such, most of the documentation and configuration for javadoc holds true for this plugin.  See Sun&#39;s documentation on the javadoc [sourcepath parameter][4].

In an area where the maven-javadoc-plugin differs in functionality, Sun&#39;s documentation for the sourcepath parameter mentions that it is possible with the javadoc utility to [generate javadoc for specific classes][5].  This capability is not available with the maven-javadoc-plugin.  An example of this is shown in Sun&#39;s documentation:

      C:&gt; cd C:\home\src\java\awt
      C:&gt; javadoc -d C:\home\html Button.java Canvas.java Graphics*.java

  [1]: http://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-javadoc-plugin/
  [2]: http://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-javadoc-plugin/javadoc-mojo.html#sourcepath
  [3]: http://web.archive.org/web/20090708154943/http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.4.2/docs/tooldocs/windows/javadoc.html
  [4]: http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.4.2/docs/tooldocs/windows/javadoc.html#sourcepath
  [5]: http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.4.2/docs/tooldocs/windows/javadoc.html#documentingclasses']

