['Use the [Tomcat Ant Tasks][1].  Catalina-ant.jar is included in most Tomcat distros.  Generally, it&#39;s good to combine this with the [try-catch Ant][2] tasks.

    &lt;taskdef name=&quot;start&quot; classname=&quot;org.apache.catalina.ant.StartTask&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;taskdef name=&quot;stop&quot; classname=&quot;org.apache.catalina.ant.StopTask&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;taskdef name=&quot;try&quot; classname=&quot;ise.antelope.tasks.TryTask&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;try&gt;
        &lt;stop url=&quot;${url}&quot;
            username=&quot;${username}&quot;
            password=&quot;${password}&quot;
            path=&quot;${path}&quot;/&gt;
        &lt;catch&gt;
            &lt;echo&gt;${path} stop failed.&lt;/echo&gt;
        &lt;/catch&gt;
    &lt;/try&gt;
     &lt;try&gt;
        &lt;start url=&quot;${url}&quot;
            username=&quot;${username}&quot;
            password=&quot;${password}&quot;
            path=&quot;${path}&quot;/&gt;
        &lt;catch&gt;
            &lt;echo&gt;${path} start failed.&lt;/echo&gt;
        &lt;/catch&gt;
    &lt;/try&gt;

If this is a pure memory issue, you might want to tweak some memory entries in the JVM startup (I&#39;ve done this often, but never written about it as clearly as [this][3] or [this][4]):

    -XX:+UseConcMarkSweepGC
    -XX:+CMSPermGenSweepingEnabled
    -XX:+CMSClassUnloadingEnabled
    -XX:MaxPermSize=256m


  [1]: http://raibledesigns.com/wiki/Wiki.jsp?page=TomcatAntTasks
  [2]: http://antelope.tigris.org/nonav/docs/manual/bk03ch07.html
  [3]: http://my.opera.com/karmazilla/blog/2007/03/13/good-riddance-permgen-outofmemoryerror
  [4]: http://raibledesigns.com/rd/entry/how_do_you_determine_a']

